==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poy
<hw>Poy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>apui</ets>,
<ets>apoi</ets>, a support, prop., staff, F. <ets>appui</ets>, fr. OF.
<ets>apuier</ets>, <ets>apoier</ets>, to support, F. <ets>appuyer</ets>,
fr. <ets>⟦agrave⟧</ets> to (L. <ets>ad</ets>) + OF. <ets>pui</ets>,
<ets>poi</ets>, a rising ground, hill, L. <ets>podium</ets>. See
<er>Podium</er>, <er>Pew</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A support; --
used in composition; <as>as, tea<ex>poy</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A ropedancer's balancing pole.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A long boat hook by which barges are propelled
against the stream.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poynado</ent>⟦br⟧
